HEADWORD: Sealskin
<hw>Seal"skin`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The skin of a seal;
the pelt of a seal prepared for use, esp. of the fur seal; also, a
garment made of this material.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

